parties datacube

Source: R/manytreaties-parties.R
parties.Rd

The manytreaties::parties datacube is a list containing 5 datasets: HUGGO, IEADB, DESTA, GPTAD, and TFDD. It is a work-in-progress, so please let us know if you have any comments or suggestions.

parties

Format

HUGGO :

A dataset with 91,673 observations and 30 variables: treatyID, stateID, Title, Begin, End, StateSignature, StateRatification, StateForce, StateEnd, Rat=Notif, Accession, Succession, Signature, Force, url, StateForce2, StateForce3, StateEnd2, ..., match, and Coder.

IEADB:

A dataset with 15,463 observations and 10 variables: stateID, treatyID, Begin, End, Title, stateSignature, Signature, Rat, Force, and ieadbID.

DESTA:

A dataset with 7,466 observations and 8 variables: stateID, treatyID, Begin, Title, Signature, Force, StateName, and destaID.

GPTAD:

A dataset with 2,192 observations and 6 variables: stateID, treatyID, Begin, Title, Signature, and Force.

TFDD:

A dataset with 1,832 observations and 6 variables: stateID, treatyID, Begin, Title, Signature, and tfddID.

For more information and references to each of the datasets used, please use the manydata::call_sources() and manydata::compare_dimensions() functions.

Source

  • Hollway, James, Henrique Sposito, and Jael Tan. 2021. International agreements for manydata.

  • Mitchell, Ron B. et al. 2020. 'What we know (and could know) about international environmental agreements'. Global Environmental Politics 20.1, pp. 103-121.

  • Duer, Andreas, Leonardo Baccini, and Manfred Elsig. 2014. 'The Design of International Trade Agreements: Introducing a New Database'. The Review of International Organizations 9.3, pp. 353-375.

  • World Bank Group. 2014. Global Preferential Trade Agreement Database (GPTAD). Online database. World Bank Group.

  • Oregon College of Earth and Oregon State University Atmospheric Science. 2021. Product of the Transboundary Freshwater Dispute Database.
